WEBVTT

00:01.291 --> 00:02.667
[narrator]
Previously on  Hellcats...

00:02.667 --> 00:04.291
You sure school's
worth all this?

00:04.291 --> 00:06.667
I'm going to graduate
pass the bar up north

00:06.667 --> 00:10.209
and work in a DA's office
where everybody talks
in flat Yankee vowels.

00:10.209 --> 00:11.625
You're applying
for a scholarship?

00:11.625 --> 00:13.084
I have one now
for cheerleading.

00:13.084 --> 00:15.417
-Cheerleading?
-Oh. Hello, Marti.

00:15.417 --> 00:16.708
Welcome to Cheertown.

00:16.708 --> 00:18.542
-Do you have a thing for Dan?
-What?

00:18.542 --> 00:20.333
-Because if you do,
I'll back off.
-No.

00:20.333 --> 00:22.000
I don't wanna create
drama here.

00:22.000 --> 00:23.417
Dan and I are just buds.

00:23.417 --> 00:25.375
I'm on a date
with half the squad.

00:25.375 --> 00:27.209
Look, the girl was
home-schooled, okay?

00:27.209 --> 00:28.625
Her parents raised her
like veal.

00:28.625 --> 00:30.959
The group thing is how her
church used to handle dating.

00:30.959 --> 00:33.750
Growing up, I figured
I'd wait until I was married
to have sex.

00:33.750 --> 00:36.750
Marriage, sex...
let's just take
one step at a time.

00:36.750 --> 00:38.000
Not worry so much.

00:38.000 --> 00:40.042
I need two pre-law students
to help me.

00:40.042 --> 00:42.000
You're in.
My law clinic starts Monday.

00:42.000 --> 00:45.250
[man]  A man been
sentenced to life in prison
for a minor burglary.

00:45.250 --> 00:47.667
You've made it clear
you don't care
if Travis is innocent.

00:47.667 --> 00:49.209
You found proof
of his innocence?

00:49.209 --> 00:51.667
I'm searching everywhere
for this Jane Loomis.

00:51.667 --> 00:53.250
Ta-da. We'd like
to talk to you

00:53.250 --> 00:55.125
about your ex-boyfriend,
Travis Guthrie.

00:55.125 --> 00:57.291
Our law clinic is looking
into his robbery conviction.

00:57.291 --> 00:59.583
I really have
nothing more to add.

00:59.583 --> 01:00.959
Thank you.

01:00.959 --> 01:02.792
