Five, six, seven, eight.

01:17.125 --> 01:20.125
♪ See the people
Walkin' down the street ♪

01:20.125 --> 01:23.583
♪ Fall in line
Just watchin' all their feet ♪

01:23.583 --> 01:26.167
♪ They don't know
Where they wanna go ♪

01:26.167 --> 01:28.667
♪ But they're
Walkin' in time ♪

01:28.667 --> 01:31.417
♪ They got the beat
We got the beat ♪

01:31.417 --> 01:34.209
♪ We got the beat ♪

01:34.209 --> 01:35.667
-Hey, I'm here.
-Oh, good.

01:35.667 --> 01:38.125
You can help me with these.

01:38.125 --> 01:40.458
They're working up
a Go-Go's routine? Really?

01:40.458 --> 01:42.041
We're setting up
for the spirit party.

01:42.041 --> 01:45.167
Oh, yeah, that.
I didn't realize it was
coming up so soon.

01:45.167 --> 01:47.166
Haven't you been reading
the  Daily Cheertown Bulletin?

01:47.166 --> 01:49.417
I'm proud to say
I didn't know we had one.

01:49.417 --> 01:51.250
[sighs]
Still, why Go-Go's?

01:51.250 --> 01:55.000
It's the 25th anniversary
of the founding of
the Hellcats in 1985.

01:55.000 --> 01:57.500
So, this year has got
an '80s theme.

01:57.500 --> 02:00.125
I like that there's
a sense of history
in the bobblehead community.

02:00.125 --> 02:02.834
Yeah, it's really hard
to make that nickname
sound complimentary.

02:02.834 --> 02:04.209
Oh, I kid the bobblehead.

02:04.209 --> 02:05.542
You think
you're being playful.

02:05.542 --> 02:07.500
No, I just like the word.
"Bobblehead."

02:07.500 --> 02:09.000
♪ We got the beat ♪

02:09.000 --> 02:10.792
♪ We got the bee-at ♪

02:10.792 --> 02:13.291
[crowd cheering]

02:14.834 --> 02:17.041
Alice, why are you
all dressed up?

02:17.041 --> 02:18.583
Something came up.

02:18.583 --> 02:19.875
I can't stay.

02:19.875 --> 02:21.834
But you promised to help.

02:21.834 --> 02:23.209
Fotogem  is doing
a style piece

02:23.209 --> 02:25.166
on the private lives
of Lancer football stars.

02:25.166 --> 02:27.375
Wow, who said
journalism is dead?

02:27.375 --> 02:29.834
It's a PR offensive from
the athletic department.

02:29.834 --> 02:32.708
They're trying to make
people forget about
that pay-for-play scandal.

02:32.708 --> 02:34.125
I couldn't care less.

02:34.125 --> 02:37.208
All I know is
I am getting my picture
in a glossy magazine.

02:37.208 --> 02:39.417
Never thought I'd see you
as a football wife.

02:39.417 --> 02:42.083
[laughs]
I am not anyone's wife.

02:42.083 --> 02:43.792
But it's a great magazine.

02:43.792 --> 02:45.042
I'm lookin' hot,

02:45.042 --> 02:46.500
Jake is gonna look dashing,

02:46.500 --> 02:48.084
and after the photo shoot,

02:48.084 --> 02:49.875
we'll go have nasty,
acrobatic sex

02:49.875 --> 02:52.000
in positions that
you can't even draw.

02:52.000 --> 02:54.917
Oh, pretty much anyone can
draw a stick figure, so...

02:54.917 --> 02:58.542
-God. Who let him in here?
-I did.

02:58.542 --> 03:00.959
I'm just pitchin' in,
aidin' the cause.

03:00.959 --> 03:04.209
Helpin' the angels of spirit
make the world
a cheerier place.

03:04.209 --> 03:07.166
God, Savannah,
does he talk that much
during sex?

03:07.166 --> 03:10.417
-I wouldn't know.
-Right. Of course
you wouldn't.

03:10.417 --> 03:12.792
Don't wait up, kids.

03:12.792 --> 03:15.084
What does that mean,
"Of course I wouldn't?"

03:15.084 --> 03:18.041
I don't like how she's gettin'
ever since she hooked up
with Jake.

03:18.041 --> 03:21.167
Anybody ever tell you
you think about Jake too much?

03:23.583 --> 03:25.166
Uh, Jake who?

03:27.667 --> 03:30.208
That's great, guys.
Smile. Big smiles.

03:30.208 --> 03:32.750
Two more shots.

03:32.750 --> 03:35.208
Great. Thank you.
We'll do singles over there.

03:35.208 --> 03:38.125
-Jake.
-Yeah?

03:38.125 --> 03:42.041
So, tell me a little
about the social life
as Lancers' QB one.

03:42.041 --> 03:43.583
[laughing]

03:43.583 --> 03:44.917
Well, it's rigorous.

03:44.917 --> 03:46.125
Work hard. Play hard.

03:46.125 --> 03:48.667
Nap every two weeks
whether I need it or not.

03:48.667 --> 03:50.291
I have
a parlor trick for you.

03:50.291 --> 03:51.708
I can name your perfume.

03:51.708 --> 03:53.834
-No way.
-Mmm-hmm.

03:55.083 --> 03:58.084
-Lolita Lempicka.
-That's amazing.

03:58.084 --> 03:59.792
-How did you do that?
-Do what?

03:59.792 --> 04:01.542
How did I charm you in
ten seconds?

04:01.542 --> 04:03.209
[laughing]

04:03.209 --> 04:04.792
Listen, you need
to meet my girlfriend.

04:04.792 --> 04:06.583
Alice. Come up here.

04:06.583 --> 04:08.125
[phone beeps]

04:09.125 --> 04:11.625
Alice, darling, meet Kelsey.

04:11.625 --> 04:13.875
A pleasure.
I love your magazine.

04:13.875 --> 04:16.916
-Alice is a cheerleader.
-Of course she is.

04:16.916 --> 04:18.166
Quarterbacks and pompom girls,

04:18.166 --> 04:20.083
it's like peanut butter
and jelly, right?

04:20.083 --> 04:22.084
Two great tastes.

04:22.708 --> 04:24.250
We're not pompom girls.

04:24.250 --> 04:25.792
Oh?

04:25.792 --> 04:28.750
Yes, we cheer at games,
but that's just
to pay the rent.

04:28.750 --> 04:30.208
We're competitive athletes.

04:30.208 --> 04:33.333
Yeah, the Hellcats
rock the sidelines
every Saturday afternoon.

04:33.333 --> 04:36.333
-Our fans just love 'em.
-You said the team competes?

04:36.333 --> 04:39.417
Yes, we're ranked seventh
overall in the southern
co-ed division

04:39.417 --> 04:43.167
and we've qualified to move on
to sectional competitions
next month.

04:43.167 --> 04:45.417
-Impressive.
-Oh, you would
think so, right?

04:45.417 --> 04:47.167
But apparently
it doesn't matter

04:47.167 --> 04:50.084
to Lancers' crack athletic
department bureaucrats.

04:50.084 --> 04:52.917
They reallocated our funds
to the volleyball team.

04:52.917 --> 04:54.500
We love our volleyball gals.

04:54.500 --> 04:57.000
Any one of 'em could kick my
butt. Know what I'm saying?

04:57.000 --> 04:59.125
[laughing]

05:00.166 --> 05:03.125
But somehow Lancer
found $3 million

05:03.125 --> 05:05.125
for Red Raymond's salary
this year.

05:05.125 --> 05:06.917
Can I steal the lovely
Ms. Verdura?

05:06.917 --> 05:09.084
Just for a second.
We'll be back in two ticks.

05:09.084 --> 05:10.166
Come here.

05:11.875 --> 05:13.333
Be right back.

05:15.000 --> 05:16.542
You're hurting my arm.

05:16.542 --> 05:18.708
What in God's name
do you think you're doing?

05:18.708 --> 05:20.208
You don't talk
to me like that.

05:20.208 --> 05:23.166
This is an article
about the football team,
the Lions,

05:23.166 --> 05:25.667
not a platform
for your cheerleading agenda.

05:25.667 --> 05:26.875
My agenda?

05:26.875 --> 05:28.792
You're gonna
go back in there, smile

05:28.792 --> 05:30.542
and you're gonna
shut your mouth.

05:30.542 --> 05:32.583
You got it?

05:32.583 --> 05:34.000
No.

05:34.000 --> 05:37.000
I don't think
I got anything.

05:38.917 --> 05:41.875
I don't care
who your daddy is.

05:41.875 --> 05:44.041
If you don't tell me
what I wanna hear right now,

05:44.041 --> 05:46.125
I will rain holy hell
upon you,

05:46.125 --> 05:48.125
you smart-mouthed
little idiot.

05:51.209 --> 05:52.458
Now tell me.

05:54.042 --> 05:55.834
Tell me.

05:57.208 --> 05:59.084
Yes, sir.

06:00.417 --> 06:01.834
Thanks, Angel.

06:04.125 --> 06:05.750
I hope this man here
has told you

06:05.750 --> 06:07.000
how pretty you look today.

06:10.042 --> 06:11.959
Thanks for all the support.

06:17.375 --> 06:18.834
[keys clacking]

06:20.875 --> 06:22.000
[knock on door]

06:22.000 --> 06:23.834
-Hey, babe.
-Hey.

06:23.834 --> 06:25.125
Can I crash with you?

06:25.125 --> 06:27.500
-Darwin needs the room.
-He hooked up again?

06:27.500 --> 06:29.291
Yeah, he met
some guy at Empire.

06:29.291 --> 06:31.208
[laughs]
It's always the quiet ones.

06:31.208 --> 06:33.500
What is in his DNA,
and where can I get some?

06:33.500 --> 06:35.625
Yeah.

06:35.625 --> 06:38.500
Yeah. Of course you can stay.
Let me just clear it
with Savannah.

06:38.500 --> 06:40.208
Hey, I swear, no funny stuff.

06:40.208 --> 06:42.042
-Yeah?
-Mmm-hmm.

06:42.042 --> 06:44.167
-Don't make rash promises.
-Hmm.

06:45.667 --> 06:47.167
Ooh.

06:54.041 --> 06:55.834
-Hey.
-Yo, M.

06:55.834 --> 06:58.542
Oh, hey, Marti,
is it cool if Dan crashes
on the floor tonight?

06:58.542 --> 07:01.667
[scoffs]
Ha. Funny story.

07:05.708 --> 07:09.000
Y'all want help fixing up
a spot on the floor for Lewis?

07:09.000 --> 07:11.042
Where?
In the closet?

07:13.834 --> 07:16.875
Oh. Oh, you two are--

07:16.875 --> 07:18.417
Don't look so scandalized.

07:18.417 --> 07:22.083
[laughing]

07:22.083 --> 07:25.333
It's, it's just that we're
all in the same room.

07:25.333 --> 07:29.084
We're not planning on having
sex with you guys in the room.

07:29.084 --> 07:32.084
Oh. Thank the Lord
for small favors.

07:32.084 --> 07:34.667
If there's a problem, I can
just take the sofa outside.

07:34.667 --> 07:36.375
No problem. It's all good.

07:36.375 --> 07:38.458
[Dan] At least
you achieved mattress.

07:38.458 --> 07:39.959
I'm sorry. What?

07:39.959 --> 07:42.125
I said at least
he achieved mattress.

07:42.125 --> 07:45.125
I know what you said.
It was a crack.

07:45.125 --> 07:47.250
No crack. Statement of fact.
He is in the bed.

07:47.250 --> 07:49.917
Because he's got
a cool girlfriend
and yours is a prude?

07:49.917 --> 07:51.083
I did not say that.

07:51.083 --> 07:53.083
I would have remembered
if he called me cool.

07:53.083 --> 07:54.166
Relax.

07:54.166 --> 07:56.708
Yeah, we're all just
slumber party pals.

07:56.708 --> 07:58.083
[laughing]

08:00.000 --> 08:01.625
Sorry.

08:09.250 --> 08:11.042
Umm.

08:14.583 --> 08:17.417
Okay, now everyone's
on eggshells.

08:17.417 --> 08:19.209
I... I'm feeling pressured.

08:19.209 --> 08:21.417
You guys want me to invite
Dan in my bed, right?

08:21.417 --> 08:23.166
Ease the tension?

08:23.166 --> 08:25.083
Nope. Not really.

08:25.083 --> 08:27.250
Do not have a dog
in that race.

08:27.250 --> 08:31.125
I'm a good girl,
and I resent being forced
to apologize for it.

08:31.125 --> 08:32.500
All right, look,

08:32.500 --> 08:35.042
nobody is asking you
to apologize.

08:35.042 --> 08:36.792
Look, why don't
I just go home?

08:36.792 --> 08:39.457
To your room you share
with your older brother
and his fiancee?

08:39.457 --> 08:41.875
That's terrible and awkward.
You say so all the time.

08:41.875 --> 08:44.834
And yet, at this moment,
it seems strangely appealing.

08:46.583 --> 08:48.000
You get the bed.
I'll take the sofa.

08:48.000 --> 08:50.834
-No, I'm not letting you--
-No, you're a guest.

08:50.834 --> 08:53.042
You get the bed.
That's how it works.

08:59.125 --> 09:01.000
Wow.

09:01.000 --> 09:03.333
Somebody's got issues.

09:03.333 --> 09:05.792
Aw, so much
for my orgy fantasy.

09:11.542 --> 09:14.291
Is it me, or is Savannah
getting weirdly intense?

09:14.291 --> 09:16.125
She's drunk
on your heady musk.

09:16.125 --> 09:18.250
-Not that drunk, sadly.
-Poor Dan Patch,

09:18.250 --> 09:21.458
finally dating a cheerleader
and she won't let you
under her skirt.

09:21.458 --> 09:23.875
I have the same problem with
Scottish bagpipe players.

09:23.875 --> 09:25.291
Savannah's a great girl.

09:25.291 --> 09:28.084
I just wish she'd lighten up
on the whole sex issue.

09:28.084 --> 09:30.917
Lighten up, as in
agree to have it with you?

09:32.208 --> 09:35.125
Not necessarily,
believe it or not.

09:35.125 --> 09:37.125
Are you saying
you don't want sex?

09:39.000 --> 09:42.000
Not if it's gonna be
under these circumstances.

09:42.000 --> 09:43.875
I'm tired
of talking about it.

09:43.875 --> 09:45.875
Am I okay with not having sex?

09:45.875 --> 09:47.792
-Do I think she's a prude?
-Hmm.

09:47.792 --> 09:50.500
If she gives it up,
will I consider marriage
down the line?

09:50.500 --> 09:53.042
-Wait. Marriage? Really?
-Subject was broached.

09:53.042 --> 09:54.625
Wow.

09:54.625 --> 09:59.167
Just the way she obsesses
over the virginity issue...
scares me.

09:59.167 --> 10:01.333
-Don't overreact.
-Yeah? Tell her that.

10:01.333 --> 10:03.542
In her head,
she's building it up

10:03.542 --> 10:06.084
into this gigantic
rite of passage

10:06.084 --> 10:08.125
that's gonna change
her life forever.

10:08.125 --> 10:09.667
It's a lot of responsibility.

10:09.667 --> 10:12.125
We know all about you
and taking responsibility.

10:12.125 --> 10:13.875
Okay, that's unkind.

10:13.875 --> 10:16.167
Look...

10:16.167 --> 10:19.000
hang on to her
with both hands, Dan Patch.

10:19.000 --> 10:20.625
She's good people.

10:20.625 --> 10:22.041
You don't think I know that?

10:22.041 --> 10:24.000
Yeah, well, remember it.

10:24.000 --> 10:26.000
Crap. I'm late.

10:26.000 --> 10:27.542
Where are you off to?

10:27.542 --> 10:28.959
State prison.

10:28.959 --> 10:30.834
[laughing]

10:30.834 --> 10:32.208
I want your life!

10:33.959 --> 10:36.125
[guitar music]

10:36.125 --> 10:38.834
Guys any closer
to springin' me
from this hole?

10:38.834 --> 10:40.542
Making progress.

10:40.542 --> 10:42.542
We've been looking
into deed records.

10:42.542 --> 10:45.167
Your old pal Jane Loomis
is homeless no longer.

10:45.167 --> 10:46.875
She lives here.

10:50.083 --> 10:52.125
Two years ago,
she was splittin' her time

10:52.125 --> 10:53.959
between a freeway underpass
and a shelter,

10:53.959 --> 10:55.542
and now she's livin'
in this palace?

10:55.542 --> 10:57.041
Huh, it's hardly a palace.

10:57.041 --> 10:58.875
Doesn't even have
a proper garage.

11:00.333 --> 11:02.125
We think it's weird, too.

11:02.125 --> 11:04.084
A homeless woman agrees
to be your alibi

11:04.084 --> 11:06.125
then recants on the stand,
incriminating you

11:06.125 --> 11:09.083
and two years later,
she's mysteriously
living the middle-class dream.

11:09.834 --> 11:11.041
Something's off.

11:11.041 --> 11:13.708
Do you think
someone bribed her to lie?

11:13.708 --> 11:15.375
Maybe.

11:15.375 --> 11:19.125
If we find out who it is,
it gets you one step closer
to gettin' out of this place.

11:19.125 --> 11:21.959
House is owned by a guy
named Bobby Overton.

11:21.959 --> 11:23.417
[Marti]
Ring a bell?

11:23.417 --> 11:25.708
I... I don't know him. Sorry.

11:25.708 --> 11:28.084
He, uh, owns
a furniture company.

11:28.084 --> 11:29.959
And you think he's in on it?

11:29.959 --> 11:31.667
Maybe.

11:31.667 --> 11:33.750
It takes a special sort
of humanitarian

11:33.750 --> 11:36.625
to rent a house to a woman
with no previous address.

11:38.458 --> 11:40.667
We'll see what
Mr. Overton has to say.

11:42.084 --> 11:44.000
[Bobby]
Real estate law?

11:44.000 --> 11:47.000
I wasn't aware
such a discipline existed.

11:47.000 --> 11:48.959
How can I help you kids?

11:48.959 --> 11:53.083
County records lists you
as the owner of a house
on May Dale Street.

11:53.083 --> 11:57.333
If you don't mind me asking,
what kind of a school project
is this?

11:57.333 --> 11:59.333
We're doing a mock court case

11:59.333 --> 12:01.333
involving, uh,
rent-control laws.

12:01.333 --> 12:04.875
We're surveying
the properties on that block
to examine the law's effects.

12:04.875 --> 12:09.333
So, uh, while it's not
specifically documented
as a rental unit,

12:09.333 --> 12:11.083
there appears to be
a tenant living there.

12:11.083 --> 12:14.000
Uh, yeah,
I did that one off the books.

12:14.000 --> 12:16.167
A favor to a friend.

12:16.167 --> 12:18.834
What the tax man don't know,
he can't tax, hmm?

12:18.834 --> 12:20.834
Oh. Yep.

12:20.834 --> 12:22.458
You're not here
to bust me, right?

12:22.458 --> 12:23.959
-Ah.
-Oh, no.

12:23.959 --> 12:25.166
No, we wouldn't dream of it.

12:25.166 --> 12:27.125
So, Jane Loomis
is your friend?

12:27.125 --> 12:28.583
Indeed she is.

12:28.583 --> 12:32.084
I met Janie Loomis
at the South Parkway Mission
down on Third Street.

12:32.084 --> 12:34.000
I volunteer there
every Sunday.

12:34.000 --> 12:39.125
Uh, pardon my French,
but life has dealt
Janie a crap hand.

12:39.125 --> 12:41.583
I had a property that had
been empty for two years,

12:41.583 --> 12:43.917
so I let her
take it over rent-free.

12:43.917 --> 12:46.667
Give her a chance to get
back on her feet, you know.

12:46.667 --> 12:50.084
How, how long has Jane
been in the house?

12:50.084 --> 12:51.834
Eh, a year or thereabouts.

12:51.834 --> 12:54.500
You know, it's a shame
your professor's

12:54.500 --> 12:57.375
got you runnin' all over town,
doin' his dirty work.

12:57.375 --> 13:00.291
All work and no play,
that's no way to live.

13:02.875 --> 13:06.167
