on the Hellcats as underdogs.

27:43.875 --> 27:45.084
[chuckles]

27:45.084 --> 27:47.375
Kelsey!
I think I love you.

27:47.375 --> 27:48.750
[chuckles]

27:48.750 --> 27:51.083
Just let me know
what I can do to help.

27:53.084 --> 27:54.625
Maybe a little more champagne.

27:54.625 --> 27:56.083
Oh, you got it.

28:00.708 --> 28:04.042
Bill Marsh wanted
that football piece.

28:04.042 --> 28:05.583
Well, you heard the woman.

28:05.583 --> 28:08.000
It was gonna get spiked
no matter what I did.

28:08.000 --> 28:10.084
I can't control what
the press decides to publish.

28:10.084 --> 28:12.000
Do you have any idea
what's gonna happen

28:12.000 --> 28:14.375
when Bill Marsh finds out
that a Lions Football piece

28:14.375 --> 28:17.166
got traded out by a piece
on the freakin' Hellcats?

28:17.166 --> 28:19.500
He's gonna figure out
my girlfriend was behind it.

28:19.500 --> 28:21.959
And he's gonna have me stuffed
and mounted on his wall.

28:21.959 --> 28:23.125
Well, that's quite the visual.

28:23.125 --> 28:25.834
I'm...I'm not
screwin' around, Alice.

28:26.333 --> 28:28.167
Oh, lighten up.

28:28.167 --> 28:30.583
Bill Marsh needs you
a lot more than you need him.

28:30.583 --> 28:31.834
That is not the point.

28:31.834 --> 28:33.583
The point is we're
supposed to be a couple.

28:33.583 --> 28:35.041
And you just stabbed me
in the back.

28:36.875 --> 28:38.834
I'm sorry you're so upset.

28:38.834 --> 28:42.291
Next time,
maybe you'll treat me with
a little bit more respect.

28:42.291 --> 28:45.125
Next time, you'll support me
when a bullying jackass

28:45.125 --> 28:48.583
attacks me in a public place
and almost makes me cry.

28:48.583 --> 28:52.000
We are supposed
to be a couple, after all.

28:55.667 --> 29:00.083
♪ Tempted but the truth
Is discovered ♪

29:00.083 --> 29:01.458
[instrumental music]

29:02.959 --> 29:05.000
Marti! Marti!

29:06.000 --> 29:07.667
I need to talk to you alone.

29:07.667 --> 29:09.708
Wow! Great '80s costume.

29:09.708 --> 29:11.000
-Urkel, right?
-No, no.

29:11.000 --> 29:12.458
He's Skippy
from  Family Ties.

29:12.458 --> 29:14.000
Yes, I remind you
of famous nerds.

29:14.000 --> 29:16.208
Funny stuff, I need to talk
to you in private.

29:16.208 --> 29:18.333
My laptop was stolen
from my dorm room.

29:18.333 --> 29:20.042
I went downstairs
to grab some cereal

29:20.042 --> 29:22.042
came back ten minutes later,
and it was missing.

29:22.042 --> 29:26.042
Uh, my TV, my Blu-ray player,
my roommate's laptop

29:26.042 --> 29:28.084
they were all still there.
My laptop, gone.

29:28.084 --> 29:30.000
Sorry to hear that.
Was it insured?

29:30.000 --> 29:31.084
No, you're not getting this.

29:31.084 --> 29:33.083
This is a warning
from Overton.

29:33.083 --> 29:35.417
Oh, you think Overton
stole the laptop?

29:35.417 --> 29:37.583
I think he'd steal back
the U2 tickets first.

29:37.583 --> 29:38.708
Probably worth more.

29:38.708 --> 29:40.708
He knows we're onto something.

29:40.708 --> 29:43.208
-Stuff goes missing from
the dorms all the time.
-Where's your laptop?

29:43.208 --> 29:45.166
Morgan, we're in
the middle of a party.

29:45.166 --> 29:46.708
Check.

29:46.708 --> 29:47.750
What?

29:54.792 --> 29:56.041
See?

29:56.750 --> 29:58.291
Safe and sound.

29:58.291 --> 30:01.500
You can report the theft
with campus security
in the morning.

30:01.500 --> 30:04.209
Right now, you should go back
to the party, have a beer.

30:04.209 --> 30:06.583
-Play some Ms. Pac-Man.
-I don't like video games.

30:10.042 --> 30:11.209
[indistinct chatter]

30:33.792 --> 30:36.333
Well, check you out,
Mr. Wall Street.

30:36.333 --> 30:39.041
Greed is good,
but that hair is fantastic.

30:39.041 --> 30:41.583
Yeah, well, just don't
light a match.

30:41.583 --> 30:42.792
[chuckles]

30:42.792 --> 30:45.875
My hand is out to lead me
to the dance floor.

30:46.834 --> 30:50.166
♪ Tell her I'll be waiting ♪

30:50.166 --> 30:53.291
♪ In the usual place ♪

30:53.291 --> 30:56.208
♪ With the tired
And weary... ♪

30:56.208 --> 30:59.042
Isn't life funny sometimes?

30:59.042 --> 31:00.458
How do you mean?

31:00.458 --> 31:04.750
I always thought
you and my baby girl
would end up together.

31:04.750 --> 31:07.084
-What?
-[chuckles]

31:07.084 --> 31:09.917
Yeah, you know,
a mother knows these things.

31:09.917 --> 31:11.084
I always think it's obnoxious

31:11.084 --> 31:13.125
when women say that,
but it's true.

31:13.125 --> 31:14.917
I'm, I'm not following.

31:14.917 --> 31:16.542
What's true?

31:16.542 --> 31:20.500
-Marti's in love with you.
-Excuse me?

31:20.500 --> 31:22.125
Yeah, she has been
since her sophomore

31:22.125 --> 31:23.959
or junior year in high school.

31:23.959 --> 31:25.458
When she got her boobs.

31:25.458 --> 31:27.209
She told me.

31:27.209 --> 31:28.625
Marti was never
in love with me.

31:28.625 --> 31:31.625
-Did you ever read her diary?
-Uh, no.

31:31.625 --> 31:34.000
Well, she used to write
these little poems.

31:34.000 --> 31:35.375
They were so sweet.

31:35.375 --> 31:38.000
Oh, damn,
the things that we do

31:38.000 --> 31:40.458
and say when we're young.

31:40.458 --> 31:43.167
I miss being your age.

31:43.167 --> 31:45.083
What else did she write?

31:45.083 --> 31:47.125
Oh, I can't tell you
my daughter's secrets.

31:47.125 --> 31:49.375
They would take away
my "good mother" card.

31:49.375 --> 31:53.167
But suffice it to say
that now that you're older

31:53.167 --> 31:56.417
who does she call late at
night when she needs advice?

31:56.417 --> 31:57.583
Not Lewis.

31:57.583 --> 31:59.500
Certainly not me.

31:59.500 --> 32:01.417
It's you.

32:01.417 --> 32:03.583
Don't you remember last year
when she had the flu.

32:03.583 --> 32:07.041
And she wouldn't let anybody
within 100 miles of her?

32:07.041 --> 32:09.333
All of a sudden,
you show up with DVDs

32:09.333 --> 32:13.209
and she's ready to spread
germs all over the damn place.

32:13.209 --> 32:15.875
That, my dear, is love.

32:15.875 --> 32:17.375
That's love.

32:17.375 --> 32:21.125
So I think it's so funny,
I mean, Marti and Lewis.

32:21.125 --> 32:24.375
And you and Savannah
whilin' away the time

32:24.375 --> 32:26.667
while Venus
and the Gods of love

32:26.667 --> 32:29.750
are gonna wave
that magic wand

32:29.750 --> 32:31.417
and make you
all straighten up.

32:31.417 --> 32:32.959
I don't think so, Wanda.

32:32.959 --> 32:35.667
Well, of course you don't,
because you're 21.

32:35.667 --> 32:37.875
And when you're 21,
you are dumb

32:37.875 --> 32:40.375
as dirt when it comes to love.

32:40.375 --> 32:44.250
I will bet you
a dollar to a doughnut...

32:44.250 --> 32:47.208
that you and Marti will be
together within ten years.

32:49.792 --> 32:52.667
-No.
-Uh. Okay.

32:52.667 --> 32:55.041
I can't give you specifics.

32:55.041 --> 32:56.500
But you have to remember that

32:56.500 --> 33:00.125
I am a woman
with inside knowledge.

33:00.125 --> 33:02.000
So you bide your time

33:02.000 --> 33:04.917
'cause my daughter
is worth the wait.

33:09.000 --> 33:11.042
I'm gonna go get a refill.

33:13.208 --> 33:16.167
♪ Your face to mine ♪

33:16.167 --> 33:17.917
♪ I can hear... ♪

33:20.125 --> 33:21.333
-Hey.
-Hey.

33:21.333 --> 33:23.708
-Wanna get out of here?
-Already?

33:23.708 --> 33:25.125
Yeah, I don't know.
I'm, I'm tired.

33:25.125 --> 33:26.458
I just wanna change,

33:26.458 --> 33:29.125
take a shower,
and veg in front of the TV.

33:29.125 --> 33:31.000
Hey, Lewis, can you
give us a minute?

33:31.000 --> 33:35.375
Uh, yeah, I'll just, uh,
make my farewell rounds.

33:35.375 --> 33:37.083
I had an interesting
conversation

33:37.083 --> 33:38.333
with Wanda just now.

33:38.333 --> 33:40.041
Well, car wrecks are
interesting by nature.

33:40.041 --> 33:41.834
What'd you guys talk about?

33:41.834 --> 33:43.083
You.

33:43.083 --> 33:45.125
Yeah?
What about me?

33:45.125 --> 33:47.291
Well, for one thing,
if you still keep a diary

33:47.291 --> 33:49.333
you need a better lock.

33:49.333 --> 33:51.834
But the other thing...

33:52.417 --> 33:54.042
Yeah.

33:55.875 --> 33:59.042
Did you ever tell your mom
you were in love with me?

34:00.000 --> 34:02.583
[scoffs]
What? No.

34:02.583 --> 34:04.000
Hold on, really think
about your answer

34:04.000 --> 34:06.208
'cause this is important.

34:06.208 --> 34:08.291
It's a party.
Wanda's drinking, I mean--

34:08.291 --> 34:11.750
She seemed
pretty lucid for Wanda.

34:11.750 --> 34:14.542
How would any of this
come up?

34:14.542 --> 34:16.000
And why are you
grilling my mom?

34:16.000 --> 34:17.208
If you have
something to ask--

34:17.208 --> 34:18.708
I'm asking you right now.

34:18.708 --> 34:22.250
Wanda seems to think
we're soulmates or something

34:22.250 --> 34:24.083
because of things
you supposedly told her.

34:24.083 --> 34:26.583
So I just wanna know.

34:26.583 --> 34:28.208
Did you or did you not...

34:28.208 --> 34:29.875
suggest to your mom
that you believed

34:29.875 --> 34:32.166
we would...end up together?

34:40.708 --> 34:42.083
No.

34:47.875 --> 34:49.000
I mean, maybe.

34:49.000 --> 34:50.625
Yeah.

34:53.417 --> 34:54.917
Look, if, if I did

34:54.917 --> 34:58.792
and that's a big if,
it was a long time ago, so...

34:58.792 --> 35:01.000
I mean, I've also been
in love with Trent Reznor

35:01.000 --> 35:03.625
Tori Amos, and, and the guy
from the Dyson
vacuum cleaner ads.

35:03.625 --> 35:05.708
-So I--
-Okay, look.

35:05.708 --> 35:08.041
I'm goin' down
a road here with Savannah.

35:11.583 --> 35:13.417
Is there any reason
I shouldn't?

35:15.375 --> 35:16.834
Like what?

35:18.500 --> 35:20.208
You tell me.

35:26.333 --> 35:28.583
I have nothing to say.

35:31.209 --> 35:33.167
Got it?

35:35.000 --> 35:36.875
I got it.

35:40.208 --> 35:42.667
You and my mom
are something...

35:44.209 --> 35:45.708
incredible.

35:47.167 --> 35:48.250
[sighs]

35:51.125 --> 35:52.417
Hey.

35:52.417 --> 35:53.875
Have you seen Savannah?

35:53.875 --> 35:56.041
I wanna introduce her
to my reporter friend.

35:56.041 --> 35:57.458
Yeah, she'll be back
in a minute.

35:57.458 --> 35:58.667
She...went to Cheertown

35:58.667 --> 36:00.542
to get her overnight bag.

36:00.542 --> 36:02.167
Oh, right.

36:02.167 --> 36:04.000
Tonight's the big night.

36:04.000 --> 36:06.792
So it is.

36:06.792 --> 36:09.291
♪ There must be a solution
To the one thing ♪

36:09.291 --> 36:11.917
♪ The one thing
We can't find ♪

36:13.667 --> 36:17.042
You ever wondered if you made
a mistake you couldn't fix?

36:18.291 --> 36:19.959
I don't believe in regret.

36:21.834 --> 36:23.750
That must be nice for you.

36:25.834 --> 36:29.167
My dad says there's
no such thing as mistakes.

36:29.167 --> 36:30.708
Only new opportunities.

36:31.417 --> 36:33.417
Smart way to look at it,
I guess.

36:33.417 --> 36:35.542
You can second guess
yourself out of anything.

36:35.542 --> 36:38.083
But...you do it enough,
you start to realize

36:38.083 --> 36:40.000
that your life
is passing you by.

36:41.291 --> 36:42.792
[Savannah] Dan.

36:45.000 --> 36:46.875
Here's your girl.

36:48.333 --> 36:50.875
Ready to go?
I have a car waiting outside.

36:55.208 --> 36:56.542
Absolutely.

36:56.542 --> 36:58.417
[chuckles]

37:06.417 --> 37:08.625
[door opens]

37:10.125 --> 37:12.166
Hey, everything okay?

37:12.166 --> 37:14.917
Yeah.
Just had a long night.

37:16.083 --> 37:17.792
You, uh...

37:17.792 --> 37:20.083
wanna make it
a little longer?

37:20.083 --> 37:21.708
Hmm?

37:27.000 --> 37:28.625
What?

37:28.625 --> 37:30.542
I'm not feeling well.

37:30.542 --> 37:32.125
I'll be fine
in the morning.

37:33.333 --> 37:35.792
-Are you sure?
-Yeah.

37:35.792 --> 37:38.167
Well, if you wanna talk
about anything--

37:38.167 --> 37:40.000
I don't.

37:40.000 --> 37:43.708
-That's fine, I'm not prying.
-I appreciate that.

37:44.959 --> 37:47.291
But if you do need
to talk about anything--

37:47.291 --> 37:49.042
I'm, I'm good.

37:52.208 --> 37:53.917
Good.

37:55.000 --> 37:56.917
Good.

38:03.000 --> 38:04.000
[sighs]

38:10.166 --> 38:11.417
Hey, Lewis!

38:11.417 --> 38:13.667
Have you seen my laptop?

38:13.667 --> 38:16.250
Lewis, have you seen
my laptop?

38:16.250 --> 38:18.084
I think somebody's
been in here.

38:20.209 --> 38:21.375
[Lewis]
Where did you leave it?

38:21.375 --> 38:22.875
[Marti] It was on my bed.

38:22.875 --> 38:24.041
[Lewis] Everybody's
still at the party.

38:24.041 --> 38:25.375
[Marti]
Who else was here?

38:25.375 --> 38:26.625
[Lewis] Building auto-locks
at night.

38:26.625 --> 38:27.792
Nobody gets in
without a key.

38:27.792 --> 38:30.167
[Marti] I know, I know.

38:45.208 --> 38:46.792
Before we go any further,
there's something

38:46.792 --> 38:48.750
I wanna tell you.

38:48.750 --> 38:50.417
Anything.

38:50.417 --> 38:53.250
I'm really excited
you're gonna be my first.

38:54.209 --> 38:55.333
Me, too.

38:56.792 --> 38:59.042
[sighs] For a while,
I was really worried

38:59.042 --> 39:01.667
that...my first time
wouldn't be special.

39:01.667 --> 39:03.209
I'd reach
a point in my life

39:03.209 --> 39:06.208
where I'd just
have to hurry up
and get it over with.

39:06.208 --> 39:07.500
Why would you do that?

39:07.500 --> 39:09.084
Because I know
it's a little weird

39:09.084 --> 39:11.125
to be a 21-year-old virgin
in this day and age.

39:11.125 --> 39:15.417
Savannah, nothing
about you is weird.

39:16.458 --> 39:17.959
You're my girl.

39:19.458 --> 39:22.167
I was starting to wonder if
the person I was waiting for

39:22.167 --> 39:24.333
was ever gonna come along.

39:24.333 --> 39:27.959
But now I know it was
the right decision to wait.

39:27.959 --> 39:30.333
Because you're the one
I've been waiting for.

39:32.250 --> 39:35.750
♪ Would you still know
The pain? ♪

39:35.750 --> 39:37.500
It's gotta be
the right person.

39:37.500 --> 39:39.875
-I believe that.
-Yeah.

39:42.417 --> 39:43.959
[door opens]

39:47.708 --> 39:49.000
Whoa!

39:49.000 --> 39:51.208
Okay, maybe I went
a little overboard.

39:51.208 --> 39:53.084
No...it's cool.

39:53.084 --> 39:55.834
It is?
It's not too much?

39:57.542 --> 39:59.000
It's perfect.

40:02.417 --> 40:04.250
Mmm.

40:04.250 --> 40:06.125
[grunts]

40:06.125 --> 40:07.875
Look at this.

40:07.875 --> 40:11.084
Great sheets.
Like, 6,000 pillows.

40:11.084 --> 40:12.959
Seriously, there is,
like, seven, eight...

40:12.959 --> 40:15.834
more pillows
than I can count.

40:15.834 --> 40:19.125
This is a good bed.

40:19.125 --> 40:21.250
It's the perfect setting
for the first time.

40:23.250 --> 40:25.417
What was your first time like?

40:25.417 --> 40:26.792
You really wanna know?

40:26.792 --> 40:28.959
Yeah, yeah, I do.

40:28.959 --> 40:31.167
It's not a very
interesting story.

40:31.167 --> 40:33.125
I don't care.

40:33.125 --> 40:35.208
It was high school.

40:35.208 --> 40:37.291
Did you love her?

40:39.083 --> 40:41.166
Yeah.

40:41.166 --> 40:43.125
Yes, I did.

40:43.125 --> 40:46.125
What do I know?
I was 16, you know?

40:49.708 --> 40:51.375
[sighs]
What are you doin'?

40:52.208 --> 40:53.667
This is a bad idea.

40:55.792 --> 40:58.084
So was it romantic?

40:58.667 --> 41:00.084
[Dan] Was what romantic?

41:00.084 --> 41:02.125
[chuckles]
Your first time.

41:02.917 --> 41:05.750
Oh...not remotely.

41:05.750 --> 41:08.583
In the back of a Buick,
middle of nowhere

41:08.583 --> 41:11.250
out off, uh, Route 51.

41:16.208 --> 41:18.000
[sighs]

41:18.000 --> 41:22.834
♪ I wanna be the one
To walk in the sun ♪

41:22.834 --> 41:24.834
♪ Girls they wanna
Have fun... ♪

41:24.834 --> 41:25.959
[door closes]

41:25.959 --> 41:27.166
Savannah?

41:27.166 --> 41:30.583
♪ Oh, girls
They wanna have fun ♪

41:30.583 --> 41:35.625
♪ That's what
They really want ♪

41:35.625 --> 41:39.875
♪ Some fun ♪

41:39.875 --> 41:44.917
♪ When the workin'
Day is done ♪

41:44.917 --> 41:47.125
♪ Girls they wanna have... ♪

41:47.125 --> 41:49.167
Savannah...

41:49.167 --> 41:50.000
Savannah!

41:50.000 --> 41:53.917
♪ Girls they
Wanna have fun ♪

